        </equation>
        <para id="id68788">Then the co-ordinates of the midpoint (<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>S</m:mi></m:math>) of the line between point <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>P</m:mi></m:math> with co-ordinates <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>;</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> and point <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>Q</m:mi></m:math> with co-ordinates <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>;</m:mo><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> is:</para>
